fields.public_access_description: This is a series of 154 ancient specimens collected in Italy in the 19th century. Marbles and other stones have been cut and polished since ancient times to produce a durable surface which comes in a huge variety of natural patterns and colours. Reference collections of different ancient marbles were a popular souvenir for visitors to Italy in the 18th and 19th centuries. These specimens were collected in the neighbourhood of Rome: while most of them could have been used for architectural decoration in the classical period, there are also imported varieties not available until the Renaissance or later. Some of the hardstones would only have been suitable for small scale pietra dura inlay work.
